{
  "video_id": "tbvUCrS5_5I",
  "title": "An economic case for protecting the planet | Naoko Ishii",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13672.0,
      "end_time": 15680.0,
      "text": "Good evening, everyone."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16204.0,
      "end_time": 18980.0,
      "text": "I am from Japan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18122.0,
      "end_time": 23550.0,
      "text": "so I&#39;d like to start with a story about Japanese fishing villages."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24671.0,
      "end_time": 31750.0,
      "text": "In the past, every fisherman was tempted to catch as many as fish as possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 32270.000000000004,
      "end_time": 35431.0,
      "text": "but if everybody did that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 35455.0,
      "end_time": 40724.0,
      "text": "the fish, common shared resource in the community, would disappear."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 41560.0,
      "end_time": 46601.0,
      "text": "The result would be hardship and poverty for everyone."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 47927.0,
      "end_time": 51228.0,
      "text": "This happened in some cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 51252.0,
      "end_time": 55934.0,
      "text": "but it did not happen in other cases."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 56694.0,
      "end_time": 58662.0,
      "text": "In these communities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 58686.0,
      "end_time": 63124.0,
      "text": "the fishermen developed a kind of social contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 63148.0,
      "end_time": 68799.0,
      "text": "that told each one of them to hold back a bit to prevent overfishing."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 69772.0,
      "end_time": 73208.0,
      "text": "The fisherman would keep an eye on each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 73896.0,
      "end_time": 78480.0,
      "text": "There would be a penalty if you were caught cheating."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 78965.0,
      "end_time": 85553.0,
      "text": "But once the benefit of a social contract became clear to everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 85577.0,
      "end_time": 89860.0,
      "text": "the incentive to cheat dramatically dropped."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 90606.0,
      "end_time": 93169.0,
      "text": "We find the same story around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 94361.0,
      "end_time": 98412.0,
      "text": "This is how villagers in medieval Europe"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 98436.0,
      "end_time": 101626.0,
      "text": "managed pasture and forests."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 102353.0,
      "end_time": 106929.0,
      "text": "This is how communities in Asia managed water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 106954.0,
      "end_time": 112524.0,
      "text": "and this is how indigenous peoples in the Amazon managed wildlife."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 113858.0,
      "end_time": 119913.0,
      "text": "These communities realized they relied on a finite, shared resource."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 121318.0,
      "end_time": 127402.0,
      "text": "They developed rules and practices on how to manage those resources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 127426.0,
      "end_time": 129854.0,
      "text": "and they changed their behavior"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 129877.99999999999,
      "end_time": 136426.0,
      "text": "so that they could continue to rely on those shared resources tomorrow"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 136450.0,
      "end_time": 138997.0,
      "text": "by not overfishing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 139210.0,
      "end_time": 140974.0,
      "text": "not overgrazing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 140998.0,
      "end_time": 145672.0,
      "text": "not polluting or depleting water streams today."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 146572.0,
      "end_time": 149604.0,
      "text": "This is a story of the commons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 149628.0,
      "end_time": 156222.0,
      "text": "and also how to avoid the so-called tragedy of the commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 157462.0,
      "end_time": 160816.0,
      "text": "But this is also a story of an economy"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 160840.0,
      "end_time": 163710.0,
      "text": "that was mainly local,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 163950.0,
      "end_time": 167436.0,
      "text": "where everybody had a very strong sense of belonging."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 169320.0,
      "end_time": 171746.0,
      "text": "Our economies are no longer local."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 172359.0,
      "end_time": 175708.0,
      "text": "When we moved away from being local,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 175732.0,
      "end_time": 179906.0,
      "text": "we started to lose our connection to the commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 180675.0,
      "end_time": 186508.0,
      "text": "We carried economic objectives, goals and systems beyond the local,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 186532.0,
      "end_time": 191444.0,
      "text": "but we did not carry the notion of taking care of the commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 193365.0,
      "end_time": 197356.0,
      "text": "So our oceans, forests,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 197380.0,
      "end_time": 201314.0,
      "text": "once very close to us as our local commons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 201338.0,
      "end_time": 204209.0,
      "text": "moved very far away from us."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 205609.0,
      "end_time": 211434.0,
      "text": "So today, we pump millions of tons of greenhouse gases into the air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 213980.0,
      "end_time": 218383.0,
      "text": "we dump plastics, fertilizers and industrial waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 218407.0,
      "end_time": 220890.0,
      "text": "into the rivers and oceans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 220914.0,
      "end_time": 224351.0,
      "text": "and we cut down forests that absorb CO2."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 225486.0,
      "end_time": 229629.0,
      "text": "We make the wild biodiversity much more fragile."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 231163.0,
      "end_time": 233839.0,
      "text": "We seem to have totally forgotten"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 233863.0,
      "end_time": 238465.0,
      "text": "that there is such a thing as global commons:"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 238489.0,
      "end_time": 243749.0,
      "text": "air, water, forests and biodiversity."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 245664.0,
      "end_time": 248828.0,
      "text": "Now, it is modern science"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 248853.0,
      "end_time": 253140.0,
      "text": "that reminds us how vital the global commons are."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 254536.0,
      "end_time": 259533.0,
      "text": "In 2009, a group of scientists proposed"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 259557.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262818.0,
      "text": "how to assess the health of the global commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 263726.0,
      "end_time": 269798.0,
      "text": "They defined nine planetary boundaries vital to our survival,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 269822.0,
      "end_time": 273275.0,
      "text": "then they measured how far we could go"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 273299.0,
      "end_time": 277878.0,
      "text": "before we cross over the tipping points or thresholds"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 277903.0,
      "end_time": 283164.0,
      "text": "that would lead us to the irreversible or even catastrophic change."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 285716.0,
      "end_time": 289621.0,
      "text": "This is where we were in the 1950s."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 291165.0,
      "end_time": 296700.0,
      "text": "We broadly remained within safe operating space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 296310.0,
      "end_time": 298235.0,
      "text": "marked by the green line."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 300196.0,
      "end_time": 302394.0,
      "text": "But look at where we are now."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 304892.0,
      "end_time": 309170.0,
      "text": "We have crossed four of those boundaries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 309194.0,
      "end_time": 311948.0,
      "text": "and we will be crossing others in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 313279.0,
      "end_time": 316461.0,
      "text": "How did we end up in this situation?"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 317957.0,
      "end_time": 321258.0,
      "text": "Well, my personal story may tell us something."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 323167.0,
      "end_time": 325316.0,
      "text": "Five years ago, I was appointed"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 325341.0,
      "end_time": 329985.0,
      "text": "as CEO of the GEF, Global Environment Facility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 330900.0,
      "end_time": 333748.0,
      "text": "but I am not a conservationist"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 333772.0,
      "end_time": 336437.0,
      "text": "or an environmental activist."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 337171.0,
      "end_time": 339188.0,
      "text": "I am an economist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 339212.0,
      "end_time": 341561.0,
      "text": "and for the last 30 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 341585.0,
      "end_time": 347440.0,
      "text": "I had worked for public finance in my home country and around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 348616.0,
      "end_time": 351450.0,
      "text": "I can tell you one thing for sure:"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 351474.0,
      "end_time": 353815.0,
      "text": "during these 30 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 353839.0,
      "end_time": 357888.0,
      "text": "the notion of the global commons never crossed my mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 358657.0,
      "end_time": 362722.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t have a single conversation about the global commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 362746.0,
      "end_time": 364300.0,
      "text": "with my colleagues."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 365244.0,
      "end_time": 369118.0,
      "text": "This tells me that the notion of the global commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 369142.0,
      "end_time": 373740.0,
      "text": "was not really entering into the big money decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 373980.0,
      "end_time": 376383.0,
      "text": "like state budgets or investment plans."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 378240.0,
      "end_time": 381914.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m wondering, why do we have this sheer ignorance"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 381938.0,
      "end_time": 383858.0,
      "text": "about the global commons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 383882.0,
      "end_time": 385961.0,
      "text": "including me, myself?"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 387835.0,
      "end_time": 391676.0,
      "text": "One possible explanation might be"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 391700.0,
      "end_time": 395840.0,
      "text": "that until recently, it didn&#39;t really matter too much."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 396394.0,
      "end_time": 400524.0,
      "text": "Even if we mess up some part of the environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 400548.0,
      "end_time": 406360.0,
      "text": "we were not fundamentally changing the functions of the earth system."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 407720.0,
      "end_time": 411630.0,
      "text": "The global commons had still enough capacity"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 411870.0,
      "end_time": 413594.0,
      "text": "to take the punches we gave them."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 414500.0,
      "end_time": 417555.0,
      "text": "In fact, the fish were still plentiful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 419325.0,
      "end_time": 423550.0,
      "text": "the fields for grazing were still vast."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 424849.0,
      "end_time": 427397.0,
      "text": "Our mistake was to assume"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 427421.0,
      "end_time": 430620.0,
      "text": "that the capacity of the earth for self-repair"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 430644.0,
      "end_time": 431952.0,
      "text": "had no limits."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 432752.0,
      "end_time": 434705.0,
      "text": "It does have limits."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 435812.0,
      "end_time": 439189.0,
      "text": "The message from the science is very clear:"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 439213.0,
      "end_time": 442443.0,
      "text": "we humans have become an overwhelming force"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 442467.0,
      "end_time": 446633.0,
      "text": "to determine the future living conditions on earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 446658.0,
      "end_time": 449959.0,
      "text": "and what&#39;s more, we are running out of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 450589.0,
      "end_time": 454656.0,
      "text": "If we don&#39;t act on them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 454680.0,
      "end_time": 457380.0,
      "text": "we will be losing the global commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 457620.0,
      "end_time": 460720.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s only our generation who are able to preserve it --"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 460744.0,
      "end_time": 462847.0,
      "text": "preserve the commons as we know them."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 464193.0,
      "end_time": 469313.0,
      "text": "Now is the time we start managing the global commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 469337.0,
      "end_time": 474908.0,
      "text": "as our parents or our grandparents managed their local commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 476851.0,
      "end_time": 479298.0,
      "text": "The first thing we need to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 479322.0,
      "end_time": 485357.0,
      "text": "is to simply recognize that we do have the global commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 485381.0,
      "end_time": 487943.0,
      "text": "and they are very, very important."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 489393.0,
      "end_time": 493291.0,
      "text": "Then we need to build the stewardship of the global commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 493315.0,
      "end_time": 495394.0,
      "text": "into all of our thinking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 495418.0,
      "end_time": 497537.0,
      "text": "our business, our economy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 497561.0,
      "end_time": 499770.0,
      "text": "our policy-making --"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 499101.0,
      "end_time": 500838.0,
      "text": "in all of our actions."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 501567.0,
      "end_time": 506991.0,
      "text": "We need to recreate the social contract of the fishing villages"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 507150.0,
      "end_time": 509135.0,
      "text": "on the global scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 511539.0,
      "end_time": 513822.0,
      "text": "But what does it mean in practice?"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 514875.0,
      "end_time": 516203.0,
      "text": "Where to start with?"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 517375.0,
      "end_time": 521429.0,
      "text": "I see there are four key economic systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 521453.0,
      "end_time": 523556.0,
      "text": "that fundamentally need to change."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 524396.0,
      "end_time": 527569.0,
      "text": "First, we need to change our cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 528298.0,
      "end_time": 533711.0,
      "text": "By 2050, two thirds of our population will live in cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 534298.0,
      "end_time": 536433.0,
      "text": "We need green cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 537920.0,
      "end_time": 540853.0,
      "text": "Second, we need to change our energy system."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 540878.0,
      "end_time": 544584.0,
      "text": "The world economy must sharply decarbonize,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 544608.0,
      "end_time": 546861.0,
      "text": "essentially in one generation."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 548500.0,
      "end_time": 552699.0,
      "text": "Third, we need to change our production-consumption system."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 553376.0,
      "end_time": 559725.0,
      "text": "We need to break away from current take-make-waste consumption patterns."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 560686.0,
      "end_time": 565524.0,
      "text": "And finally, we need to change our food system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 565548.0,
      "end_time": 568114.0,
      "text": "what to eat and how to produce it."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 568644.0,
      "end_time": 571486.0,
      "text": "And all of those four systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 571510.0,
      "end_time": 575708.0,
      "text": "are putting enormous pressure on the global commons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 575732.0,
      "end_time": 578422.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s also very difficult to flip them."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 578840.0,
      "end_time": 580918.0,
      "text": "They are extremely complex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 580942.0,
      "end_time": 583610.0,
      "text": "with many decision-makers, actors involved."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 585753.0,
      "end_time": 588641.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s take the example of the food system."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 590556.0,
      "end_time": 594199.0,
      "text": "Food production is currently responsible"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 594223.0,
      "end_time": 597381.0,
      "text": "for one quarter of greenhouse gas emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 598190.0,
      "end_time": 602205.0,
      "text": "It is also a main user of the world&#39;s water resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 602775.0,
      "end_time": 608766.0,
      "text": "In fact, 70 percent of today&#39;s water is used to grow crops."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 609740.0,
      "end_time": 614447.0,
      "text": "Vast areas of tropical forest are used for agriculture."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 615550.0,
      "end_time": 618757.0,
      "text": "This deforestation drives extinction."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 618781.0,
      "end_time": 623741.0,
      "text": "In fact, we are losing species 1,000 times faster"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 623765.0,
      "end_time": 624979.0,
      "text": "than the natural rate."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 626200.0,
      "end_time": 629923.0,
      "text": "And on top of all of that bad news,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 629947.0,
      "end_time": 634127.0,
      "text": "one third of food produced today globally"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 634151.0,
      "end_time": 635341.0,
      "text": "is not eaten."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 635768.0,
      "end_time": 637485.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s wasted."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 639449.0,
      "end_time": 642401.0,
      "text": "But there is the good news,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 642426.0,
      "end_time": 643576.0,
      "text": "good signs."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 644220.0,
      "end_time": 647580.0,
      "text": "Coalitions of stakeholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 647604.0,
      "end_time": 652481.0,
      "text": "are now coming together to try to transform the food system"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 652505.0,
      "end_time": 654890.0,
      "text": "with one shared goal:"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 654914.0,
      "end_time": 659466.0,
      "text": "how to produce enough healthy food for everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 659490.0,
      "end_time": 660986.0,
      "text": "at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 661100.0,
      "end_time": 664130.0,
      "text": "to try to cut, to sharply reduce,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 664154.0,
      "end_time": 668395.0,
      "text": "the footprint from the food system on the global commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 670983.0,
      "end_time": 672681.0,
      "text": "I had an opportunity"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 672706.0,
      "end_time": 677660.0,
      "text": "to fly over the Indonesian island of Sumatra,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 677900.0,
      "end_time": 679758.0,
      "text": "and I saw with my own eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 679782.0,
      "end_time": 681939.0,
      "text": "the massive deforestation"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 681963.0,
      "end_time": 686161.0,
      "text": "to make room for palm oil plantations."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 687178.0,
      "end_time": 691879.0,
      "text": "By the way, palm oil is included in thousands of food products"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 691903.0,
      "end_time": 693504.0,
      "text": "we eat every day."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 693528.0,
      "end_time": 696599.0,
      "text": "The global demand for palm oil is just increasing."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 698168.0,
      "end_time": 702304.0,
      "text": "In Sumatra, I met smallholder farmers"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 702328.0,
      "end_time": 706946.0,
      "text": "who need to make a day-to-day living from growing oil palm."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 707803.0,
      "end_time": 710652.0,
      "text": "I met global food companies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 710676.0,
      "end_time": 712527.0,
      "text": "financial institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 712551.0,
      "end_time": 714606.0,
      "text": "and local government officials."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 716350.0,
      "end_time": 721846.0,
      "text": "All of them told me that they can&#39;t make the change by themselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 721870.0,
      "end_time": 727339.0,
      "text": "and only by working together under a kind of new contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 727363.0,
      "end_time": 728926.0,
      "text": "or a new practice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 728950.0,
      "end_time": 732418.0,
      "text": "do they have a chance to protect tropical forests."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 733891.0,
      "end_time": 738935.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s so encouraging to see, at least for the last few years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 738959.0,
      "end_time": 744666.0,
      "text": "this new coalition among these committed actors along the supply chain"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 744691.0,
      "end_time": 748801.0,
      "text": "come together to try to transform the food system."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 749392.0,
      "end_time": 752497.0,
      "text": "In fact, what they are trying to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 752521.0,
      "end_time": 758940.0,
      "text": "is to create a new kind of social contract to manage the global commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 761697.0,
      "end_time": 765390.0,
      "text": "All changes start at home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 765630.0,
      "end_time": 767641.0,
      "text": "at your place and at my place."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 768626.0,
      "end_time": 772292.0,
      "text": "At GEF, Global Environment Facility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 772316.0,
      "end_time": 774753.0,
      "text": "we have now a new strategy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 774777.0,
      "end_time": 778283.0,
      "text": "and we put the global commons at its center."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 780552.0,
      "end_time": 783257.0,
      "text": "I hope we won&#39;t be the only ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 784273.0,
      "end_time": 789877.0,
      "text": "If everybody stays on the sidelines, waiting for others to step in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 789901.0,
      "end_time": 793560.0,
      "text": "the global commons will continue to deteriorate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 793584.0,
      "end_time": 797566.0,
      "text": "and everybody will be much worse off."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 798388.0,
      "end_time": 802904.0,
      "text": "We need to save ourselves from the tragedy of the commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 804451.0,
      "end_time": 810930.0,
      "text": "So, I invite all of you to embrace the global commons."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 810801.0,
      "end_time": 814641.0,
      "text": "Please do remember that global commons do exist"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 814665.0,
      "end_time": 817500.0,
      "text": "and are waiting for your stewardship."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 818609.0,
      "end_time": 821807.0,
      "text": "We all share one planet in common."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 822546.0,
      "end_time": 824871.0,
      "text": "We breathe the same air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 824895.0,
      "end_time": 826887.0,
      "text": "we drink the same water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 826911.0,
      "end_time": 831752.0,
      "text": "we depend on the same oceans, forests, and biodiversity."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 832974.0,
      "end_time": 836379.0,
      "text": "There is no space left on earth for egoism."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 837144.0,
      "end_time": 842659.0,
      "text": "The global commons must be kept within their safe operating space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 842683.0,
      "end_time": 846889.0,
      "text": "and we can only do it together."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 848710.0,
      "end_time": 849317.0,
      "text": "Thank you so much."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 849341.0,
      "end_time": 852920.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}